criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age 18 to 85 years;

          -  Diagnosis of acute ischemic stroke with mechanical thrombectomy procedure < 8 hours
             from onset of symptoms/ last known well;

          -  Large Vessel Occlusion on CT or MRI in the anterior cerebral vasculature up to A1, M1,
             or M2 or the posterior cerebral vasculature;

          -  ASPECTS 6 - 10 or volume of diffusion restriction < 50 mL;

          -  Use of the Q Aspiration Catheter as the first line treatment according to the IFU;

          -  Signed informed consent by patient or legally authorized representative.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Occlusions in multiple vascular territories, extracranial occlusion or tandem
             occlusion;

          -  Evidence of dissection in the carotid or target artery for treatment;

          -  Evidence of recent/fresh haemorrhage on presentation;

          -  Unwilling to agree to a 3-month follow up visit.
